00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:24.720
Mycelium is a vegetative part of
the fungi consisting of a mass

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:28.210
of branching threadlike hyphae.

00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:32.390
The white or transparent hyphae
may be minute forming a colony

00:20:32.390 --> 00:20:34.540
that's too small to see

00:20:34.540 --> 00:20:37.750
or the mycelium might
be extensive appearing

00:20:37.750 --> 00:20:42.530
like very fine fluffy white
threads over the surface.

00:20:42.530 --> 00:20:46.390
Mycelium is considered
a single organism.

00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:51.210
Typically mold secrete
hydraulic enzymes mainly

00:20:51.210 --> 00:20:56.610
from the hyphae tips to
degrade complex biopolymers,

00:20:56.610 --> 00:21:00.460
biopolymers such as starch,
cellulose and lignin,

00:21:00.460 --> 00:21:03.230
our stuff right into
simpler monomers

00:21:03.230 --> 00:21:05.550
that can be absorbed by hyphae.

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:09.000
Molds play a vital role in
causing the decomposition

00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:11.990
of organic matter
that enables recycling

00:21:11.990 --> 00:21:16.590
of nutrients throughout the
ecosystems, it's good for us.

00:21:16.590 --> 00:21:22.070
When mold is ready to reproduce
small treelike fruiting bodies

00:21:22.070 --> 00:21:24.480
form on the ends of the hyphae.

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:27.690
The dusty texture of
many molds is caused

00:21:27.690 --> 00:21:31.990
by the profuse production of
asexual spores called conidia

00:21:31.990 --> 00:21:34.740
that grow on the
tree-shaped hyphae.

00:21:34.740 --> 00:21:36.820
The mode of formation
and the shape

00:21:36.820 --> 00:21:39.720
of these spores is
traditionally used as the method

00:21:39.720 --> 00:21:41.700
