00:40:56.650 --> 00:40:58.250
The image of a commercial,

00:40:58.250 --> 00:41:00.720
this image of a commercial
ethylene oxide chamber was

00:41:00.720 --> 00:41:03.050
provided by Sterigenics.

00:41:03.050 --> 00:41:06.880
The effectiveness of ethylene
oxide sterilization is dependent

00:41:06.880 --> 00:41:10.280
on load density,
gas concentration,

00:41:10.280 --> 00:41:12.990
steam inject, and
the cycle time.

00:41:12.990 --> 00:41:15.890
Each of these factors have to
be correctly applied in order

00:41:15.890 --> 00:41:19.150
for the sterilization
process to be effective.

00:41:19.150 --> 00:41:23.330
Ethylene oxide is non-damaging
to paper as verified

00:41:23.330 --> 00:41:25.560
in the 1960's by
Francois [inaudible].

00:41:25.560 --> 00:41:31.530
This is a schematic of a
gamma radiation chamber

00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:35.030
that was also provided
by Sterigenics.

00:41:35.030 --> 00:41:37.450
You can see that it's a
simple system actually,

00:41:37.450 --> 00:41:44.180
it's a lead shell with a core
of nuclear material inside.

00:41:44.180 --> 00:41:47.980
And the stuff that you need
to sterilize passes by that.

00:41:47.980 --> 00:41:51.630
Gamma radiation sterilization
is a simpler process

00:41:51.630 --> 00:41:53.360
than ethylene oxide.

00:41:53.360 --> 00:41:56.370
The density of the product
determines the cycle time

00:41:56.370 --> 00:42:00.150
and the dosage required
in the radiator.

00:42:00.150 --> 00:42:01.850
The validation process
is shorter,

00:42:01.850 --> 00:42:04.850
so it may cost less
than ethylene oxide.

00:42:04.850 --> 00:42:09.900
However, gamma radiation
cleaves covalent bonds,

00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:11.660
which makes it absolutely
damaging

00:42:11.660 --> 00:42:14.960
to cultural property,
just a heads up.

00:42:14.960 --> 00:42:18.800
At the end of the
